ions in the region in ways that account for popular agency.Lisbon rising will be of interest not only to students of twentieth-century European history, but across disciplines to students of democratisation, social movements and citizenship in political science and sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocratizationzPortugalxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial movementszPortugalzLisbonxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aCarnation Revolution.  aCold War politics.  aEuropean post-war period.  aEuropean twentieth century.  aLisbon urban social movement.  aPopular Democratic Party.  aPortuguese Revolution.  aSocialist Party.  aballot box.  acivilian parties.  aelectoral legitimacy.  aimminent coups.  aliberal democracy.  aliberalisation.  apopular collective actors.  apopular mobilisation.  apopular movement.  arevolutionary legitimacy.  aurban citizenship.1 aPinto, Pedro Ramos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610305540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526103055423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526103055/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles